Barcelona legend, Xavi Hernandez, has named the five Premier League clubs he would consider managing. The former midfielder is currently taking his first steps into management with Qatari side, Al-Sadd, which he joined in May on a two-year deal. Xavi has helped the side up to third in the table, having guided the outfit to six wins in their last seven games. But he is already eyeing up a potential switch to England, with five giants on his wish list. “Obviously if I had to choose, I would choose a big team, City or United, Chelsea, Arsenal or Tottenham. “Also, [Jurgen] Klopp and [Mauricio] Pochettino and Unai Emery, many people who have gone there are doing an extraordinary job,” Xavi told Sky Sports. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.